1
00:00:06,980 --> 00:00:10,300
♪The stars in the sky shine bright♪

2
00:00:10,300 --> 00:00:14,660
♪The rippling water reflects your face♪

3
00:00:14,940 --> 00:00:18,340
♪No one knows the struggle in my mind♪

4
00:00:18,340 --> 00:00:22,020
♪I act calm as I say hi♪

5
00:00:22,020 --> 00:00:24,140
♪In two different worlds♪

6
00:00:24,140 --> 00:00:26,060
♪we're both rushing ahead♪

7
00:00:26,060 --> 00:00:29,820
♪Thinking the view at the top
would leave us breathless♪

8
00:00:29,820 --> 00:00:33,860
♪As memories fade like shattered pieces♪

9
00:00:33,860 --> 00:00:37,620
♪I still find myself drawn to you♪

10
00:00:37,620 --> 00:00:41,420
♪In a crowd of people,
with nowhere to land♪

11
00:00:41,420 --> 00:00:45,460
♪Your presence is my island,
my solid ground♪

12
00:00:45,460 --> 00:00:50,220
♪I know where you are,
but act like I don't care♪

13
00:00:50,220 --> 00:00:53,580
♪My heart beats for you,
yet I leave it unsaid♪

14
00:00:55,420 --> 00:00:58,700
[This World Is Not Real]
[Load game]

15
00:00:58,740 --> 00:01:01,700
[Episode 13]

16
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:07,480
Do you know what year it is?

17
00:01:08,070 --> 00:01:09,070
Do you know where you are now?

18
00:01:10,280 --> 00:01:12,090
Of course, it's 2020.

19
00:01:14,430 --> 00:01:15,790
In the real world,

20
00:01:16,620 --> 00:01:18,210
it's actually 2023 now.

21
00:01:19,140 --> 00:01:20,180
Three years ago,

22
00:01:20,930 --> 00:01:22,140
you had a car accident.

23
00:01:23,140 --> 00:01:24,060
Right now,

24
00:01:24,590 --> 00:01:26,090
you're still
in the hospital, unconscious.

25
00:01:28,090 --> 00:01:29,420
This isn't funny at all.

26
00:01:29,420 --> 00:01:31,640
Yes, I did ask
some strange questions, but...

27
00:01:31,850 --> 00:01:33,040
But you've had doubts too.

28
00:01:35,090 --> 00:01:35,760
Right?

29
00:01:40,310 --> 00:01:41,590
How can you prove it?

30
00:01:45,980 --> 00:01:50,120
[Ice Cream & Tea]

31
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:50,790
What?

32
00:01:54,590 --> 00:01:54,980
You...

33
00:02:07,430 --> 00:02:07,900
You...

34
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:51,310
Remember that neural physics engine

35
00:02:51,310 --> 00:02:54,120
you wanted to build for "Daydream"?

36
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:55,180
Well, you succeeded.

37
00:02:56,080 --> 00:02:56,860
Right now,

38
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:59,520
you're in a world built by Dreamscape,
the engine you created.

39
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:02,840
And this world is called

40
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:04,970
"Qing Wan's Forest".

41
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:21,740
[The Real World]
Complaints have been surging recently.

42
00:03:21,740 --> 00:03:23,000
Over 500 players

43
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,300
have reported lagging

44
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:25,810
when trying to exit "Qing Wan's Forest".

45
00:03:25,810 --> 00:03:27,030
Lagging when exiting?

46
00:03:27,030 --> 00:03:29,060
The engineers are looking for bugs.

47
00:03:29,060 --> 00:03:30,310
Since Miss Qing fell into a coma,

48
00:03:30,310 --> 00:03:31,810
no one has been able

49
00:03:31,810 --> 00:03:33,800
to upgrade the core system
of Dreamscape.

50
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:35,710
We're only able to do minor bug fixes.

51
00:03:36,590 --> 00:03:38,370
If we keep getting stuck like this...

52
00:03:38,370 --> 00:03:39,560
I'll figure something out.

53
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:40,590
Also, Mr. Lin,

54
00:03:40,590 --> 00:03:42,620
I've heard Stone Network is developing

55
00:03:42,620 --> 00:03:44,680
a massively multiplayer online
dream-based game

56
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:47,410
and offering top dollar globally
for talent and technology.

57
00:03:50,750 --> 00:03:51,970
Currently, no one but Qing Wan

58
00:03:52,690 --> 00:03:54,240
can create something like Dreamscape.

59
00:03:59,020 --> 00:04:00,360
So, you're saying

60
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:01,370
"Daydream"

61
00:04:02,180 --> 00:04:04,240
was the prototype
for "Qing Wan's Forest"?

62
00:04:06,250 --> 00:04:06,840
Yes.

63
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:09,120
It's the most popular game

64
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:10,470
in the real world right now.

65
00:04:11,300 --> 00:04:13,680
Xian Game Group's success
in the gaming industry

66
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:15,120
is all thanks to you.

67
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:16,390
Me?

68
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:18,920
I designed "Qing Wan's Forest"?

69
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:20,750
That's impossible.

70
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:25,180
You created gameplay that
revolutionized the industry.

71
00:04:25,180 --> 00:04:27,920
You deserved the Purple Pupil Award
for that game.

72
00:04:28,750 --> 00:04:31,480
Game Designer of the Year,

73
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:32,620
Qing Wan?

74
00:04:33,740 --> 00:04:34,860
[Game Designer of the Year: Qing Wan]

75
00:04:34,860 --> 00:04:35,600
Mr. Lin,

76
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:39,370
is there really a designer with my name?

77
00:04:39,370 --> 00:04:40,390
That designer is you.

78
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:42,330
So I really did win

79
00:04:42,930 --> 00:04:44,310
that Purple Pupil Award?

80
00:04:48,920 --> 00:04:50,660
Everything you're seeing here

81
00:04:50,660 --> 00:04:51,630
is fake.

82
00:04:52,310 --> 00:04:55,190
Lin Xian created all this to trap you.

83
00:04:55,190 --> 00:04:57,240
Even Deng and Qing Tian

84
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:58,420
are fake.

85
00:04:59,390 --> 00:05:00,330
What about you?

86
00:05:00,750 --> 00:05:01,890
Are you also fake?

87
00:05:01,890 --> 00:05:03,330
I'm here to help you get out.

88
00:05:03,330 --> 00:05:04,390
Lin Xian is deceiving you.

89
00:05:06,860 --> 00:05:07,510
But...

90
00:05:10,370 --> 00:05:12,330
I don't think he'd do that to me.

91
00:05:13,010 --> 00:05:14,870
But many things don't add up,

92
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:18,130
like how he keeps disappearing,

93
00:05:19,370 --> 00:05:21,240
and how everything he does
feels familiar.

94
00:05:22,810 --> 00:05:24,510
That car accident three years ago...

95
00:05:25,540 --> 00:05:27,250
Why don't I remember any of it?

96
00:05:29,770 --> 00:05:30,920
Who do you think

97
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:33,160
benefits the most
from your memory losses?

98
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:35,500
Mr. Lin?

99
00:05:37,250 --> 00:05:38,660
But how can I

100
00:05:38,660 --> 00:05:40,600
be trapped in my own dream?

101
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:41,740
After the car accident,

102
00:05:41,740 --> 00:05:43,750
Lin Xian feared you'd wake up
and challenge him

103
00:05:43,750 --> 00:05:45,770
for control of the game,
his company's biggest success,

104
00:05:45,770 --> 00:05:48,180
so he connected
the Dreamscape engine you built

105
00:05:48,180 --> 00:05:49,070
to your brain

106
00:05:50,390 --> 00:05:52,000
to keep you from waking up.

107
00:05:55,950 --> 00:05:56,720
But

108
00:05:58,750 --> 00:06:00,870
I keep having flashes...

109
00:06:03,690 --> 00:06:05,160
of me being with him.

110
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:06,220
They're all fake.

111
00:06:06,220 --> 00:06:08,920
Lin Xian implanted those memories

112
00:06:09,750 --> 00:06:11,070
to control you

113
00:06:11,890 --> 00:06:12,860
and pull you deeper into this world.

114
00:06:18,930 --> 00:06:20,630
So how do you plan
to get me out of here?

115
00:06:21,700 --> 00:06:25,820
[The Real World]

116
00:06:45,450 --> 00:06:46,750
Keep acting normal

117
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:48,100
when you see Lin Xian.

118
00:06:48,770 --> 00:06:49,860
I'll get you out of here.

119
00:07:04,450 --> 00:07:05,330
Mr. Lin?

120
00:07:07,180 --> 00:07:07,980
Where's He Fan?

121
00:07:09,370 --> 00:07:10,180
I don't know.

122
00:07:10,690 --> 00:07:11,510
I haven't seen him.

123
00:07:12,220 --> 00:07:13,660
But he was just here.

124
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,570
The moment he showed up,

125
00:07:16,570 --> 00:07:18,270
He Fan vanished.

126
00:07:18,870 --> 00:07:19,570
Could this

127
00:07:20,070 --> 00:07:21,870
really be my dream?

128
00:07:23,130 --> 00:07:24,620
We'll need to work late tonight.

129
00:07:24,620 --> 00:07:26,890
"Qing Wan's Forest"
needs a system upgrade.

130
00:07:27,630 --> 00:07:29,800
Why am I the one doing the upgrade?

131
00:07:31,100 --> 00:07:32,630
If you see Lin Xian,

132
00:07:33,100 --> 00:07:34,330
act normal.

133
00:07:34,980 --> 00:07:36,070
If he finds out

134
00:07:36,890 --> 00:07:38,070
you've learned about the truth,

135
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:41,250
you'll be in danger.

136
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:44,370
Okay.

137
00:07:46,450 --> 00:07:47,160
Can you handle it?

138
00:07:48,390 --> 00:07:50,130
It's a bit complicated.
I'll try my best.

139
00:08:00,510 --> 00:08:01,600
I'll get you something to eat.

140
00:08:07,300 --> 00:08:08,540
Is everything

141
00:08:08,540 --> 00:08:10,370
he's done for me really just an act?

142
00:08:18,220 --> 00:08:18,920
What's wrong?

143
00:08:19,630 --> 00:08:20,370
Having trouble?

144
00:08:23,930 --> 00:08:25,040
Why don't you eat first?

145
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:50,760
I'm tired.

146
00:08:51,980 --> 00:08:53,000
Have a few bites of this,

147
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:53,880
and I'll take you home.

148
00:08:54,980 --> 00:08:55,380
No need.

149
00:08:57,160 --> 00:08:58,310
But it's very late.

150
00:08:58,310 --> 00:09:00,030
I'll finish the rest tomorrow.

151
00:09:02,380 --> 00:09:03,030
Qing Wan.

152
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:07,620
Lin Xian,

153
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:09,860
is there anything else you want to say?

154
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:12,710
But she's really scared right now.

155
00:09:12,980 --> 00:09:14,620
If she starts doubting her reality,

156
00:09:14,620 --> 00:09:15,930
will that affect the outcome?

157
00:09:15,930 --> 00:09:17,410
If the unexpected event

158
00:09:17,410 --> 00:09:18,860
seems too unusual,

159
00:09:19,310 --> 00:09:21,020
the brain might choose to forget it

160
00:09:21,740 --> 00:09:22,620
as a way to protect itself.

161
00:09:25,860 --> 00:09:27,000
You've got a package.

162
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:27,640
Thanks.

163
00:09:28,790 --> 00:09:29,410
Mr. Lin,

164
00:09:29,740 --> 00:09:31,140
you need to be patient.

165
00:09:31,950 --> 00:09:33,480
If she doesn't recognize you
in the dream,

166
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:34,530
she still won't know

167
00:09:34,530 --> 00:09:35,860
who you are when she wakes up.

168
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:44,160
No.

169
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:08,120
♪The stars in the sky shine bright♪

170
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:12,360
♪The rippling water reflects your face♪

171
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:16,200
♪No one knows the struggle in my mind♪

172
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:19,880
♪I act calm as I say hi♪

173
00:10:19,880 --> 00:10:23,800
♪In two different worlds,
we're both rushing ahead♪

174
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:27,720
♪Thinking the view at the top
would leave us breathless♪

175
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:31,680
♪As memories fade like shattered pieces♪

176
00:10:31,680 --> 00:10:35,440
♪I still find myself drawn to you♪

177
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:39,240
♪In a crowd of people,
with nowhere to land♪

178
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:43,240
♪Your presence is my island,
my solid ground♪

179
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:46,000
♪I know where you are♪

180
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:48,200
♪But act like I don't care♪

181
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:51,160
♪My heart beats for you,
yet I leave it unsaid♪

182
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:55,420
♪Passion and loneliness
carve our memories♪

183
00:10:55,420 --> 00:10:59,340
♪The moonlight by the lighthouse
leaves no trace♪

184
00:10:59,340 --> 00:11:01,140
♪For you, I'd cross mountains and seas♪
